{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Fade-Through with Confirmation Toast\n      On 3rd vote: Content fades out (~200ms) → toast pill appears: \"Vote recorded ✓ — New matchup\" → new content fades in (~300ms). ~500ms total.\n      On flag: Same fade-through, but toast changes to \"Voice flagged ⚑ — New matchup\" with a red-tinted accent instead of the default. Optionally, the flagged card border briefly flashes red before the fade begins to give instant feedback on which card was flagged.\n      \n        Pros\n          Fast and clean (~500ms)\n          Toast text handles both messages naturally\n          Red-tinted toast for flags is a subtle but clear distinction\n          Simplest to implement — same animation, different toast content/color\n        \n        Cons\n          Less dramatic distinction between vote vs flag\n          Subtle — some users might still miss it","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1775069682513}
